## google-services.json Setup

This file is required for Firebase integration (Crashlytics, Analytics, Performance).

### Steps:
1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com/
2. Create a new project (or use an existing one)
3. Add an Android app with package name: `dev.spyglass.android`
4. Download the generated `google-services.json`
5. Place it in this directory: `app/google-services.json`
6. Uncomment the Firebase dependencies in `app/build.gradle.kts`
7. Uncomment the Firebase plugin apply lines in `app/build.gradle.kts`

Note: `google-services.json` is gitignored and should never be committed.
